      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CALM LEGEND (1) opened her career in pleasing fashion two weeks ago, finishing second and beaten 1.5 metres over 1720m at Dubbo. Has the benefit of a good draw. Her last-start form is good enough to put her right in the finish. THE NEEDY QUEEN (3) is back from a break of seven months and looks to be right up to the mark following a placing in a recent trial. Will enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. Sure to be right there at the finish. MILLION DOLLAR HAT (7) is stepping out for the first time. By Million Dollar Cam and hails from the D G Rusten stable. May need luck at some stage extracting from the inside of the second row. Placed in a recent trial. Any push in betting will add to the confidence. SOME JEWEL (6) was in the money two starts ago then things went wrong last start when she broke and finished a distant last over 1730m at Bathurst. Meets a similar line up so if she behaves a big run is likely.",
